This is almost certainly due to using a transport database file that 
was created on another platform. If your transport database is an 
MS-DOS text file and you try use it with ck2cti on a unix or linux 
system, it will fail, and it will likely fail also if you use a 
unix-created transport database on an MS-DOS / Windows system.  The 
problem is that MS-DOS uses two non-printing characters to denote the 
end of a line (CR LF) and unix uses only one (LF).  So a DOS text file 
when read on a unix system appears to have extra CR characters, and 
this confuses ck2cti. This has been fixed in version 1.6.0, which is 
still in development and hasn&#39;t been released, but is available through 
CVS. Otherwise, convert your transport database to have the correct 
line endings for text files on your system.  Often this can be done 
just be opening it in MS Word, and saving it as a text file.

